description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, experienced and motivated Clinical Psychologist with a passion for working with young people within Neurodevelopmental diagnoses as well as working in the Newham CAMHS Intake (Front Door) Team. You will be part of two busy and dynamic pathways one which provides a specialist CAMHS service for young people with a wide variety of conditions which co present with Moderate LD, ASD and or ADHD, and the other which is where all of our new referrals are processed as well as being provided with triage assessments, brief interventions, workshops and online self-help resources. You will be working with creative and dedicated staff in both pathways and have the opportunity to work at the very heart of Newham CAMHS as well as being provided with opportunities for community based working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Newham CAMHS is a multi-disciplinary team with a Care Pathway model of service delivery. The team consists of Child &amp; Adolescent Psychiatrists, Clinical Psychologists, Specialist Mental Health Nurses, Child &amp; Adolescent Psychotherapists, Family Therapists and Administrative staff who are committed to developing innovative and effective ways of working. This is a busy, interesting, and varied job working with children and their families in LAC and Core CAMHS treatment pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The community served is multi-ethnic and culturally diverse and we welcome applicants who are skilled at working with the richness and complexity of this multicultural context. The Child and Adolescent Mental health Service is part of the Specialist Services Directorate in the East London NHS Foundation Trust, rated an Outstanding Trust by the Care Quality Commission. There are good links with Education, Childrens Social Care and voluntary sector organisations locally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
